<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-19T11:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-19T11:48:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/1890: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jones</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-19T11:00:00-05:48"><hi rend="italic">July 19, 1919</hi>, [<hi rend="italic">11
                                            a.m.</hi>]</date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July
                                        20, 11.16 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Believed to be in peril of life and limb, General Saturnino Medal has
                                taken refuge temporarily in the Legation. No demand has been made on
                                me for release by the Government. Most prominent men under political
                                charge brutally treated and placed in penitentiary and I believe
                                lives in peril. Please advise me definitely in the premises
                                immediately after enciphering [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] the
                                above. Silverio Lainez, Lopez Padilla and Colonel Raimundo
                                Valladares [also given refuge].</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jones</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>